(Translated by Google) Brilliant idea from the town hall to integrate this park into new constructions, it makes life easier for families who live nearby, daycare centers serving the area, retirees, very good for young people too and it even attracts people who do not live in the area. It combines the useful with the pleasant. It's a good move, well done.

(Translated by Google) large and suberpe borough park. The best equipped I have seen. Chalet, toilets (but never open), water games, real climbing wall, sports equipment, exercise equipment for adults, winter sports and several varied play modules. All very recent and located in a new development.

There is also a beautiful and too rare artistic integration. In addition one can contemplate a view of the mountains surrounding the metropolis.

The park is animated with various activities during the year.

Unfortunately, and I hope to be wrong for the future, the place seems conducive to acts of vandalism.

In short, a model park.

grand et suberpe parc d'arrondissement. Le mieux équipé que j'ai vu. Le tout très récent et situé dans un nouveau développement.

On y trouve aussi une belle et trop rare intégration artistique. De plus on peut y contempler une vue sur les montagnes entourant la métropoles.

Le parc est animé de diverses activités  durant l'année.

Malheureusement, et j'espère avoir tort pour l'avenir, les lieux semblent propice aux actes de vandalisme.

Bref un parc modèle.

(Translated by Google) Beautiful family park. Several spaces for outdoor training. Children's games are good. There are outdoor water games, the kids liked it. Several areas to sit and a cabin with toilets nearby. There are two outdoor concrete ping-pong tables available to all.

The only complaint is that there is no mature tree, it is a relatively new park and therefore, it is drastically lacking shaded areas. There is not a bench in the shade. If you want a space in the shade, you have to sit on the ground under one of the anemic trees.

We had the full apm and the kids asked us to go back. Do not forget your bathing suits!

Le seul reproches, c'est qu'il n'y a pas d'arbre matures, c'est un parc relativement neuf et par le fait même, il manque drastiquement d'espaces ombragés. Il n'y a pas un banc à l'ombre. Si vous voulez un espaces à l'ombre, il faut s'asseoir par terre sous un des arbres anémiques.

On y a passé l'apm au complet et les enfants nous ont demandé d'y retourner. N'oubliez pas vos costumes de bain!

at the base of the hill, an open pit mine, very nice landscaping, a small road for runners, a soccer field, basketball, and a climbing wall covered with pretty paintings, as well as a superb outdoor training equipment available to athletes.

there are three playgrounds, very fun, one for the little ones and the other for the bigger ones, with several small integrated courses. An aquatic area, for the summer, which separates the two fields. An environment where it is good to get some fresh air, and to meet new people, which is fun, when you are parents, of only child, and that your friends do not have children, it is l ideal for your little ones to socialize and have fun. So we really enjoyed getting together with the family
